text:
East 92nd Street, east side, north of Skidmore Lane, showing in the right foreground, (N .E. corner), is the Skidmore's store (Nos. 1919-1927 East 92nd Street) and post office; from 1860-1873. In the background, may be seen the steeple of St. Matthews German Lutheran Church, which was erected in
1879.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

On the OldNYC map Skidmore's store is shown on Skidmore Ave. As noted above Skidmore's home & store was on east 92nd st. and Skidmore lane.

East 92nd Street, east side, south from Skidmore Lane, showing at the
right, the Grace Methodist Church.
June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collectdon.

1193-1195 East 92nd Street, east side, between Skidmore Lane and Flatlands Ave. A view of frame houses.

July 6, 1933

P.L. Sperr
